@startuml
skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam linetype ortho

title Serverless Todo Application - Deployment Architecture

actor "User" as User
actor "DevOps Engineer" as DevOps

package "Frontend Layer" {
    component "React UI" as UI {
        [App.js]
        [TodoList.js]
        [NewTodoForm.js]
        [config.js]
        [client.js]
        [render.js]
    }
}

package "AWS Cloud Infrastructure" {
    package "Static Hosting Layer" {
        component "S3 Bucket" as S3 <<AWS S3>> {
            [HTML]
            [CSS]
            [JavaScript]
        }
    }

    package "API Layer" {
        component "API Gateway" as APIGW <<AWS API Gateway>> {
            [/{proxy+} Endpoint]
        }
    }

    package "Compute Layer" {
        component "Lambda Function" as Lambda <<AWS Lambda>> {
            [index.js]
            [GET Handler]
            [PUT Handler]
            [DELETE Handler]
        }
    }

    package "Data Layer" {
        component "DynamoDB Table" as DB <<AWS DynamoDB>> {
            [Todo Table]
            [Todo Items]
        }
    }
}

package "Infrastructure as Code" {
    component "Serverless Framework" as SLS {
        [serverless.yml]
        [IAM Roles]
        [Environment Variables]
        [Resource Definitions]
    }
}

package "Deployment Methods" {
    component "Click-Ops Approach" as ClickOps {
        [Manual AWS Console]
        [Step-by-step Setup]
    }
    component "Serverless Approach" as SLSDeploy {
        [Automated Deployment]
        [CLI Commands]
    }
}

User -down-> S3 : HTTPS Request\n(Static Content)
S3 -up-> User : HTML/CSS/JS

User -down-> UI : Interacts
UI -down-> APIGW : API Calls\n(HTTPS REST)
APIGW -down-> Lambda : Proxy Request\n(/{proxy+})
Lambda -down-> DB : CRUD Operations\n(Read/Write)
DB -up-> Lambda : Data Response
Lambda -up-> APIGW : HTTP Response\n(JSON)
APIGW -up-> UI : API Response

SLS .right.> S3 : Deploys Static\nWebsite
SLS .down.> APIGW : Provisions\nAPI Endpoints
SLS .down.> Lambda : Deploys\nFunction Code
SLS .down.> DB : Creates\nDynamoDB Table

ClickOps .right.> S3 : Manual Setup\nvia Console
ClickOps .down.> APIGW : Manual\nConfiguration
ClickOps .down.> Lambda : Manual\nDeployment
ClickOps .down.> DB : Manual\nCreation

DevOps -down-> ClickOps : Uses for\nLearning
DevOps -down-> SLSDeploy : Uses for\nAutomation
SLSDeploy -right-> SLS : Executes\nsls deploy

note right of S3
  **Static Website Hosting**
  - Hosts React UI
  - Serves HTML, CSS, JavaScript
  - Public read access
  - Cost-effective storage
end note

note right of APIGW
  **REST API Gateway**
  - HTTP endpoint facade
  - Proxy pattern: /{proxy+}
  - Routes to Lambda
  - CORS enabled
end note

note right of Lambda
  **Serverless Compute**
  - Node.js runtime
  - CRUD operation handlers
  - Stateless execution
  - Auto-scaling
end note

note right of DB
  **NoSQL Database**
  - Stores todo items
  - Serverless scaling
  - Pay-per-request
end note

note bottom of SLS
  **Infrastructure as Code**
  - Defines all AWS resources
  - Version controlled config
  - Repeatable deployments
  - Manages IAM permissions
end note

note bottom of ClickOps
  **Manual Deployment**
  - AWS Console based
  - Educational approach
  - Step-by-step learning
  - Bootcamp training method
end note

note bottom of SLSDeploy
  **Automated Deployment**
  - CLI-based deployment
  - Production-ready approach
  - Single command deploy
  - Best practice method
end note

@enduml
